# Alexanarch License

Alexanarch is a content + code repository. Different parts have different licenses.

## Content (deposits, papers, articles, datasets, documentation)

All scholarly content in this repository — every deposit under `/data/`, `/s/records/`, `/data/texts/`, the protocol documents at `/api/`, and the long-form documentation files (`AGENTS.md`, `DEPOSIT-FLOW.md`, `WORKPLAN-*.md`, etc.) — is licensed under **Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY-4.0)** unless an individual deposit declares a different open license in its registry entry.

License text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

Individual deposits may declare alternative open licenses (CC-BY-SA-4.0, CC0-1.0) in their registry `license` field. The deposit-level declaration overrides this repository-level default for that deposit's bytes specifically.

## Code (generators, scripts, workflows, templates)

All source code in this repository — every file under `/scripts/`, `/.github/`, generator code, page templates, and renderers — is licensed under **MIT** unless a file declares otherwise in its header.

